data.value:

Credits:
Main programming: Thomas Neumann
Additional programming: Oliver Ickler
Documentation: Thomas Neumann (based on the one written by Jaakko Leikas)

¤CPhil Wright ¤CPeter William Wagner, Simon Coghlan and Thomas Bolon ¤CMark Heath ¤CAdam Hathcock ¤CDave Gandy ¤COliver Ickler ¤COzkan Sezer, Alice Rowan and Miodrag Vallat ¤CTucker Byars and Jeremy Yudkin ¤CNicolas Franck (Gryzor) ¤CSylvain "Asle" Chipaux ¤CWilfred Bos ¤CJens-Christian Huus ¤CMichael van Grunz ¤CRaph99 / Thanys ¤CFanoush ¤CAdrien Destugues ¤CRobert Baron ¤CAnd to all you users out there :-)
Features in NostalgicPlayer:
¤1¤CSupports ¤¤ module formats ¤CMost accurate player ¤CEdit and save your favorite lists of modules ¤CPossible to set latency on visuals so they sync to the audio ¤CSee and play the module samples on the keyboard ¤CSave samples from modules to disk ¤CCan load packed files, including archives ¤CShows the module length, no matter what type it is ¤CSave your favorite modules as sample files
Formats supported:
¤U¤F
¤BStreamer agents installed:
¤U¤T
¤BSample converters installed:
¤U¤S
¤BModule converters installed:
¤U¤M
¤BOutput agents installed:
¤U¤O

¤U¤I

¤U¤D

data.value: When a module error is reached

data.value: Skip file and remove from list

data.name: IDS_SETTINGS_MODULES_SHOWING_MODULEINFO_ORDER
data.value: In which order to activate tabs in Module Information window

data.name: IDS_SETTINGS_OPTIONS_GENERAL_SEPARATEWINDOWS
data.value: Separate each window in task switcher

data.name: IDS_SETTINGS_OPTIONS_GENERAL_SHOWWINDOWSINTASKBAR
data.value: Show all windows in task bar

data.name: IDS_SETTINGS_OPTIONS_GENERAL_USEDATABASE
data.value: Use database to store module information

data.name: IDS_TIP_FAVORITE_ADD
data.value: Adds selected modules to the current play list

data.name: IDS_TIP_FAVORITE_REMOVE
data.value: Removes the selected modules from the favorite list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_ADD
data.value: Add new modules to the list. The modules will be added in the bottom or right before the first selected module in the list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_DISK
data.value: Shows a pop-up menu where you can read and write the module list to disk

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_DOWN
data.value: Move all the selected items one item down. If you hold down shift while pressing the button, all the selected modules will be moved to the bottom of the list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_EJECT
data.value: Pressing once, ejects the current playing module. Pressing twice, it will clear the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_FAVORITES
data.value: Opens the favorite song system window where you can see the number of times of the modules you have played

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_FAVORITES_DISABLED
data.value: To enable this feature, you need to activate the database in the settings

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_FORWARD
data.value: Moves to the next position. If on the last position, the next module is loaded instead

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_INFO
data.value: Press the left mouse button over here to switch between elapsed and remaining time

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_LIST
data.value: Shows a pop-up menu where you can do different things on the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_MODULELOOP
data.value: When active, the current playing module will play forever

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_NEXTMOD
data.value: Loads the next module in the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_PLAY
data.value: Adds new modules to the module list. The module list will be cleared before the new modules are added

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_POSITIONSLIDER
data.value: Shows the current position in the playing module. Press the left mouse button on the rectangle and hold it while moving the mouse to the left or right to change the position

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_PREVMOD
data.value: When pressing in the first 2 seconds of a module, the previous module in the list will be loaded. If you press the button after the first 2 seconds, the module will start over again

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_REMOVE
data.value: Remove the selected modules from the list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_REWIND
data.value: Rewind to the previous position. If on first position, the previous module is loaded instead

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_SAMP
data.value: Opens the sample info window where you can see a lot of information about the samples in the current playing module

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_SORT
data.value: Shows a pop-up menu, where you can select different things to do on the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_SWAP
data.value: Will swap two selected modules in the list. Select the two modules you want to swap and press this button

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_TIME
data.value: Shows the total time of items selected + the total time in the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_TOTAL
data.value: Shows the selected number of items + the total number of items in the module list

data.name: IDS_TIP_MAIN_UP
data.value: Move all the selected items one item up. If you hold down shift while pressing the button, all the selected modules will be moved to the top of the list

data.name: IDS_MODLIBRARY_PLAYIMMEDIATELY_CHECKBOX
data.value: Play immediately (otherwise just add to playlist)
